{"id": 10640, "date": "1988-01-17T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1988-01-17T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=10640"}, "modified": "2026-02-07T14:49:04", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-07T22:49:04", "slug": "matr-jon-bon-jovi-and-bruce-springsteen-who-says-you-cant-go-home", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/01/17/matr-jon-bon-jovi-and-bruce-springsteen-who-says-you-cant-go-home/", "title": {"rendered": "Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>I&#8217;m not a big Bon Jovi fan, but I do love their song, &#8220;Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home,&#8221; from their 2005 <em>Have a Nice Day</em> album. That&#8217;s probably because it sounds just like a Bruce Springsteen song.</p>\n<p>Seriously, just listen to the lyrics and tell me that Jon wasn&#8217;t channeling Bruce when he wrote it:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/abzbVFuxigg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>So I was pretty psyched when Jon asked Bruce to join him when he played &#8220;Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home&#8221; at the\u00a0<em>12-12-12</em> benefit concert for the victims of Hurricane Sandy.</p>\n<p>Sure enough, the song fit Bruce like a glove. Watch and see&#8211;it&#8217;s a fantastic performance:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NQWFklgKA_E?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>As it turns out, &#8220;Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home&#8221; was made for a duet. In fact, Jon Bon Jovi recorded and filmed\u00a0<em>two\u00a0</em>versions of it for the same album. You&#8217;ve seen the first at the top of this post; here&#8217;s the second, in a country arrangement with Jennifer Nettles:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/5CeX5VEo10c?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>I gotta say: Bruce turned in a great performance, but the best &#8220;Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home&#8221; duet award has to go to Jon and Jennifer.</p>\n<p><strong>Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> December 12, 2012 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> December 12, 2012 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 June 22, 2019</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce joins Jon Bon Jovi on &#8220;Who Says You Can&#8217;t Go Home,&#8221; a song that sounds like Bruce could have written it himself.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 66218, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_track